1. Universal Commerce Protocol (UCP)
What is it?

UCP is a common language for shopping.

Think of it as Google Translate for online stores.

Example Without UCP

Store A shows products like:

{
  "item_name": "Black T-Shirt",
  "cost": 799
}

Store B shows:

{
  "product": "Black Tee",
  "price": 750
}

An AI agent must learn both formats.

This becomes messy.

Example With UCP

UCP converts everything into one standard format:

{
  "name": "Black T-Shirt",
  "price": 799,
  "size": "M"
}

Now every store looks the same to the AI.

Real-Life Analogy

Suppose:

One person speaks Hindi
One speaks English
One speaks French

A translator sits between them.

Person A
     ↓
 Translator
     ↓
Person B

UCP is that translator.

What UCP Does

When the AI says:

"Find black T-shirts under ₹1000"

UCP helps it:

✅ Read merchant catalogs
✅ Compare products
✅ Add items to cart
✅ Build orders

2. Agent Payments Protocol (AP2)
What is it?

AP2 is the payment system for AI agents.

Think of it as a secure digital wallet.

Problem Without AP2

Imagine giving your AI access to your credit card.

You ask:

"Buy a ₹500 T-shirt."

But the AI accidentally buys:

₹50,000 laptop

Not good!

AP2 Prevents This

Before the AI spends money, AP2 checks rules.

Example rules:

Maximum spending: ₹1000

Allowed categories:
✓ Clothing
✓ Books

Blocked categories:
✗ Electronics
✗ Jewelry

The AI cannot break these rules.

Real-Life Analogy

Suppose parents give a child:

Pocket money = ₹500

Rules:

Can buy:
✓ Snacks
✓ School supplies

Cannot buy:
✗ Video games
✗ Expensive gadgets

The child can spend only within limits.

AP2 works similarly for AI agents.

What is an Encrypted Handshake?

The paragraph mentions:

encrypted handshakes

This means both sides verify each other securely.

Example:

AI Agent  ←→ Payment System

They exchange secret encrypted information.

This confirms:

✅ Agent is genuine
✅ Merchant is genuine
✅ Payment request is authentic

Simple Analogy

Like entering an OTP while making a payment.

You enter OTP
      ↓
Bank verifies you
      ↓
Payment approved

The handshake is a machine-to-machine version of that.

What are User Guardrails?

Guardrails are spending rules set by the user.

Example:

Daily limit: ₹2000

Only buy:
- Groceries
- Medicines

Ask permission for:
- Purchases above ₹500

The AI must obey these rules.

Complete Flow Example

Suppose you tell your AI:

"Order a black T-shirt under ₹1000."

Step 1: Search Products
AI
 ↓
UCP
 ↓
Amazon, Flipkart, Myntra

UCP translates all store catalogs into one format.

Step 2: Build Order

AI finds:

Black T-Shirt
Price: ₹799
Size: M

Creates order.

Step 3: Check Payment Rules

AP2 checks:

